<paragraph id="8628475BFFB18502FF13FB31FBD0FAC9" blockId="22.[136,1452,1195,1366]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FF13FB31FEE9FB75" bold="true" box="[189,294,1231,1257]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB18502FE88FB31FDD5FB75" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[294,538,1231,1257]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="colothrix">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FE88FB31FDD5FB75" box="[294,538,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Myoxanthus colothrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB18502FCC6FB2EFBF2FB75" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[872,1085,1231,1257]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parahybunensis">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FCC6FB2EFBF2FB75" box="[872,1085,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">M. parahybunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the sheaths on the basal half of the ramicauls are completely covered with trichomes 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FCA8FB0AFCD2FA91" box="[774,797,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. smooth, and it has a toothed white column 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FABBFB0AFAE3FA91" box="[1301,1324,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. untoothed with purple wings and white oblong lip with a pair of conspicuous longitudinal keels emerging near the middle on the disc 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FF12FAC2FF1CFAC9" box="[188,211,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. subpandurate lip with purple margins and microscopical keels on the disc.
</paragraph>
